  "exercises": "<div class=\"pt-6 font-sans\">\n    <!-- Lesson Title -->\n    <div class=\"text-center px-4 mb-12\">\n        <h1 class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-gray-800\">Lesson 13: Practice Exercises</h1>\n        <p class=\"mt-2 text-lg text-sky-600 font-medium\">Let's practice cleaning up those messy denominators!</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Exercise 1 -->\n    <div class=\"exercise-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2\">Exercise 1: The Magic Multiplier</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4\">To rationalize the denominator of <strong>5 / √3</strong>, what \"special form of 1\" should you multiply it by?</p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Finding the Multiplier:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 1:</strong> Identify the irrational part of the denominator, which is √3.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 2:</strong> To eliminate √3, we need to multiply it by itself (√3).</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 3:</strong> To create a \"special form of 1\", we must put this term over itself.</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: You should multiply by <strong>√3 / √3</strong>.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <!-- Exercise 2 -->\n    <div class=\"exercise-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2\">Exercise 2: Rationalize and Simplify</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4\">Rationalize the denominator of <strong>10 / √5</strong>.</p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Solving the Expression:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 1:</strong> Multiply the numerator and denominator by √5.</p>\n                <p class=\"font-mono text-lg ml-6 mt-1 text-gray-700\">(10 / √5) × (√5 / √5) = (10√5) / 5</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2 mt-2\"><strong>Step 2:</strong> The result is (10√5) / 5. Notice that the rational numbers (10 and 5) can be simplified.</p>\n                <p class=\"font-mono text-lg ml-6 mt-1 text-gray-700\">10 / 5 = 2</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: 2√5</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Exercise 3 -->\n    <div class=\"exercise-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2\">Exercise 3: Find the Perfect Partner</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4\">What is the conjugate of the expression <strong>(4 - √11)</strong>?</p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Finding the Conjugate:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">The conjugate is found by keeping the two terms the same and flipping the sign between them.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">The original sign is a minus, so the new sign will be a plus.</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: (4 + √11)</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <!-- Exercise 4 -->\n    <div class=\"exercise-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2\">Exercise 4: Rationalize the Binomial</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4\">Rationalize the denominator of <strong>2 / (√3 + 1)</strong>.</p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Solving the Expression:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 1:</strong> The conjugate of (√3 + 1) is (√3 - 1).</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Multiply the top and bottom by the conjugate.</p>\n                <p class=\"font-mono text-lg ml-6 mt-1 text-gray-700\">[2 / (√3 + 1)] × [(√3 - 1) / (√3 - 1)]</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2 mt-2\"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Calculate the numerator and denominator.</p>\n                 <ul class=\"list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-2\">\n                    <li>Numerator: 2 × (√3 - 1) = 2√3 - 2</li>\n                    <li>Denominator: (√3 + 1)(√3 - 1) = (√3)² - 1² = 3 - 1 = 2</li>\n                </ul>\n                <p class=\"mb-2 mt-2\"><strong>Step 4:</strong> The result is (2√3 - 2) / 2. We can divide every term by 2 to simplify.</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: √3 - 1</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <!-- Exercise 5 -->\n    <div class=\"exercise-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2\">Exercise 5: True or False?</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4\">To rationalize the denominator of <strong>1 / (2√5)</strong>, you should multiply by <strong>(2√5) / (2√5)</strong>.</p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Analyzing the Statement:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">While multiplying by (2√5) / (2√5) is not mathematically wrong, it's not the most efficient way.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">The only part of the denominator that is irrational is <strong>√5</strong>. We only need to eliminate that part.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">The simplest and most efficient multiplier would be just <strong>√5 / √5</strong>.</p>\n                <p class=\"text-sm italic mt-4 text-gray-500\">Let's see why: (1 / 2√5) × (√5 / √5) = √5 / (2 × 5) = √5 / 10. This is the simplest method.</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: False. While it would work, it's not the most efficient method. You only need to multiply by the irrational part, which is √5 / √5.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <!-- Exercise 6 -->\n    <div class=\"exercise-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2\">Exercise 6: The Final Check</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4\">A student rationalizes <strong>3 / (√6 - √3)</strong> and gets an answer of <strong>(√6 + √3)</strong>. Are they correct? Show your work to verify.</p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Verifying the Answer:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 1:</strong> The conjugate of (√6 - √3) is (√6 + √3).</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Multiply top and bottom by the conjugate.</p>\n                <p class=\"font-mono text-lg ml-6 mt-1 text-gray-700\">[3 / (√6 - √3)] × [(√6 + √3) / (√6 + √3)]</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2 mt-2\"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Calculate the numerator and denominator.</p>\n                 <ul class=\"list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-2\">\n                    <li>Numerator: 3 × (√6 + √3) = 3√6 + 3√3</li>\n                    <li>Denominator: (√6)² - (√3)² = 6 - 3 = 3</li>\n                </ul>\n                 <p class=\"mb-2 mt-2\"><strong>Step 4:</strong> The result is (3√6 + 3√3) / 3. We can divide every term in the numerator by 3.</p>\n                  <p class=\"font-mono text-lg ml-6 mt-1 text-gray-700\">√6 + √3</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: Yes, the student is correct.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n</div>\n<!--end-of-code-block-->",
